HEADWORD: Exeunt
<hw>Ex"e*unt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., 3d pers. pl. pres. of
<ets>exire</ets> to go out.]</ety> <def>They go out, or retire from the
scene; <as>as, <ex>exeunt</ex> all except Hamlet</as>. See 1st
<er>Exit</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

